<item>
            <title>[PIG-4046] PiggyBank DBStorage DATETIME should use setTimestamp with java.sql.Timestamp</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4046</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Pig 0.12.1 PiggyBank DBStorage (contrib/piggybank/java/src/main/java/org/apache/pig/piggybank/storage/DBStorage.java), the code uses the wrong setter and Java data type for the SQL DATETIME datatype.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DATETIME has both date and time, so should use java.sql.Timestamp instead of java.sql.Date (which zeros the time fields).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;replace line 121&lt;br/&gt;
          case DataType.DATETIME:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ps.setDate(sqlPos, new Date(((DateTime) field).getMillis()));&lt;br/&gt;
            sqlPos++;&lt;br/&gt;
            break;&lt;br/&gt;
with&lt;br/&gt;
          case DataType.DATETIME:&lt;br/&gt;
+            ps.setTimestamp(sqlPos, new Timestamp(((DateTime) field).getMillis(&lt;br/&gt;
)));&lt;br/&gt;
            sqlPos++;&lt;br/&gt;
            break;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;CentOS 6.5&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
